{"comments":"NoisePersistence - amplitude decay factor between octaves in FBM.\n\nRange: 0.0 to 1.0 (clamps)\n- **0.0**: Higher octaves have no contribution (single octave)\n- **0.5**: Each octave has half the amplitude (standard, smooth)\n- **0.7**: Octaves contribute more (rougher, more chaotic)\n- **1.0**: All octaves equal amplitude (very rough)\n\nControls how much each octave contributes to the final noise.\nLower persistence = smoother result. Higher persistence = rougher result.\nStandard value is 0.5 (also called H = 1.0 in some papers).\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoisePersistence"],"NoisePersistence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[48,58],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/NoisePersistence.purs","start":[48,1]},"title":"eqNoisePersistence"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoisePersistence"],"NoisePersistence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[49,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/NoisePersistence.purs","start":[49,1]},"title":"ordNoisePersistence"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoisePersistence"],"NoisePersistence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[52,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/NoisePersistence.purs","start":[51,1]},"title":"showNoisePersistence"}],"com